type: scenario
name: kaijo/ssh-bruteforce-slow-pfsense
description: >
  Detects slow SSH bruteforce attacks on pfSense systems by monitoring
  distributed or low-frequency authentication failures typical for stealthy
  attackers. Designed for FreeBSD/OpenSSH log formats used by pfSense CE/Plus.

author: kaijo
license: MIT
version: 0.1.6

labels:
  service: sshd
  platform: pfSense
  attack_type: bruteforce
  speed: slow

tags:
  - pfSense
  - SSH
  - Security
  - Bruteforce
  - FreeBSD

events:
  - authentication_failed
  - invalid_user
